tickets.description: NBA Preseason - Utah Jazz at Houston Rockets

injuries.longComment: Sensabaugh lit it up at the Salt Lake City Classic earlier this month but didn't appear in any Las Vegas games due to right knee soreness. The Ohio State product will aim for a larger role in his third NBA season after averaging 10.9 points, 3.0 rebounds and 1.5 assists on 45.9 percent shooting and 42.2 percent from three across 20.2 minutes in 71 regular-season games (15 starts) during the 2024-25 campaign.
injuries.shortComment: Sensabaugh (knee) did not appear in Friday's 105-92 Summer League loss to the Bulls.

injuries.longComment: Filipowski dominated during the Las Vegas Summer League, including a 35-point, 11-rebound double-double during an overtime loss to the Spurs on Monday. The 2024 second-round pick had a solid rookie season, averaging 9.6 points and 6.1 rebounds on 50.2 percent shooting in 21.1 minutes across 72 regular-season games (27 starts). Filipowski could see a larger role in Year 2 after the departure of John Collins, but Utah also added Jusuf Nurkic and Kevin Love to their frontcourt depth.
injuries.shortComment: Filipowski has been shut down for the remainder of the Las Vegas Summer League due to rest purposes, Andy Larsen of The Salt Lake Tribune reports Wednesday.

injuries.longComment: Kessler entered concussion protocols April 3, and it will end him sidelining him for the Jazz's final five games of the regular season. Oscar Tshiebwe and Kyle Filipowski will serve as Utah's primary big men for Sunday's regular-season finale in Walker's absence. The third-year big man out of Auburn put up solid numbers for the Jazz this season, but injuries and reconditioning caused him to miss 17 of the Pelcians' 33 games since Jan. 1. With Utah failing to qualify for the postseason, Kessler will finish the 2024-25 regular season averaging 11.1 points, 12.2 rebounds, 1.7 assists and 2.4 blocks in 30.0 minutes per game across 58 outings.
injuries.shortComment: Kessler (concussion) has been ruled out for Sunday's game against the Timberwolves.

injuries.longComment: Hendricks operation was done at the University of Utah's Orthopedic center, and it appears to have gone smoothly. The 20-year-old is a candidate to return to action at some point during the 2025-26 season. Coach Will Hardy reinforced Hendricks' future with the organization last week, expressing that the injury "doesn't take away anything he's done to this point. He's developed as a player and as a young man...this is far from over for him."
injuries.shortComment: Hendricks underwent surgery on his broken right leg and dislocated ankle Wednesday, Andy Larsen of The Salt Lake Tribune reports.
